



Type of Dynamic Routing Protocols:
A)IGP(Interior Gateway Protocol): 
    01) DISTANCE VECTOR (Algorithom Type): 
        The routers only learn the 'distance'(metric) and 'vector'(direction, the next-hop router) for each route.
        It only learn/know the information that its neighbors tell it('routing by rumor').
	  a> RIP   (Routing Information Protocol)
	  b> EIGRP (Enhanced Interior Gateway Routing Protocol)
    02) LINK STATE (Algorithom Type): 
        Each router creates a independently 'connectivity map' to calculate the best routes to each destination of the network 
        and advertises this information until all neighbors develop the same map of the network. 
	--Faster than Distance Vector protocol but Use more resources(CPU) because more information is shared.
	a> OSPF  (Open Shortest Path First)
	b> IS-IS (Intermediate System to Intermediate System)
B)EGP (Exterior Gateway Protocol)
    01) PATH VECTOR (Algorithom Type)
        a> BGP(Border Gateway Protocol)  


ROUTING INFORMATION PROTOCOL(RIP)
=================================
All Routers and LANs networke Addess have to include in a ROUTER that we configuring.

ROUTER: 0
----------
en
config t
router rip
network 20.0.0.0       (Router 1 Network/Address)
network 30.0.0.0       (Router 2 N/A)
network 192.168.1.0    (OWN LAN N/A)
network 192.168.2.0    (Router 1 LAN N/A)
network 192.168.3.0    (Router 2 LAN N/A)

ROUTER: 01
----------
en
config t
router rip
network 10.0.0.0      (Router 0 N/A)
network 30.0.0.0
network 192.168.1.0
network 192.168.2.0
network 192.168.3.0


ROUTER: 02
----------
en
config t
router rip
network 10.0.0.0
network 20.0.0.0
network 192.168.1.0
network 192.168.2.0
network 192.168.3.0


